<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fable1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fable,</orth> subst. 1) a fiction: <cit><quote>these antique --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>but that's a f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.286" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 286</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a lie (euphemistically): <cit><quote>sans f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 76</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I recount no f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 111</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>